            <h3 class="title_36 mt-4"> What Are Cookies?</h3>
            <p>Cookies are small text strings that the Site sends to the user's device — whether a computer, smartphone, or tablet — where they are stored and subsequently sent back to the same Site the next time the same user visits it.</p>

            <h3 class="title_36 mt-4"> What Are Cookies Used For?</h3>
            <p>The use of cookies on the Site offers several advantages, including: (i) facilitating the user's browsing and access to the Site's features; (ii) avoiding the need to reconfigure general preferences each time the Site is accessed; (iii) enabling improvement of the services provided through the Site, as a result of the analysis of information obtained through the cookies installed; and (iv) supporting relevant marketing activity based on the user's browsing behaviour.</p>

            <h3 class="title_36 mt-4">Which Categories of Cookies Are Used on This Site?</h3>
            <p class="mt-3">The cookies used on the Site may be distinguished by the following criteria:</p>

            <p class="mt-3"><b>a) Based on who manages them:</b></p>
            <ul class="features_list mt-2">
                <li><b>First-party cookies</b> are cookies installed directly by Najmuddin Trading through the Site. The Data Controller processes the data collected from first-party cookies for its own purposes.</li>
                <li><b>Third-party cookies</b> are cookies installed through the Site by external service providers. These are controlled entirely by the relevant third party in accordance with their own privacy and cookie policies. Third parties may use cookies to track user behaviour on the Site and across other websites, particularly for marketing purposes.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mt-3"><b>b) Based on how long they remain active:</b></p>
            <ul class="features_list mt-2">
                <li><b>Session cookies</b> store information only for the duration of a browsing session and are deleted automatically when the browser is closed.</li>
                <li><b>Persistent cookies</b> are stored on the user's device and remain active until their specific expiry date or until manually deleted by the user.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mt-3"><b>c) Based on purpose:</b></p>
            <ul class="features_list mt-2">
                <li><b>Strictly necessary cookies</b> are essential for the Site to function and cannot be switched off. They do not require prior consent. Without them, the Site cannot operate correctly.</li>
                <li><b>Analytics or performance cookies</b> are used to obtain statistical information, in an aggregated and anonymous manner, on the number of users accessing the Site and how it is used. Without the user's consent, Najmuddin Trading will not be able to improve the Site based on information from the user's visit.</li>
                <li><b>Functional cookies</b> enable specific features and integrations on the Site, such as the WhatsApp chat widget. Without these cookies, some features may not function properly.</li>
                <li><b>Profiling or targeting cookies</b> are used to build a profile of the user's interests and browsing behaviour in order to support relevant content delivery on third-party platforms. If the user does not consent to these cookies, less targeted content may be shown on external platforms, though this does not affect the browsing experience on the Site itself.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="title_36 mt-4"> Which Cookies Does the Site Use?</h3>

            <p class="mt-3"><b>Strictly Necessary Cookies</b></p>
            <p>These cookies are required for the basic operation of the Site. They are set in response to actions taken by the user, such as submitting an enquiry form or setting cookie preferences. They cannot be disabled and do not require consent. Without them, the Site cannot function correctly.</p>

            <p class="mt-3"><b>Analytics Cookies — Google Analytics 4</b></p>
            <p>Google Analytics 4 is used to collect anonymous, aggregated information about how visitors interact with the Site, including pages visited, time spent, and navigation patterns. This data is used solely to improve the Site. No personally identifiable information is collected through these cookies. These are both first-party and third-party cookies. For further information on how Google processes data, please refer to the <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

            <p class="mt-3"><b>Functional Cookies — WhatsApp Widget</b></p>
